B.K8=new A.yM("mental_warrior","Mental Warrior","A self-improvement app that helps users build a stronger, more disciplined mindset through structured daily habits, motivation tools, and personal growth tracking \u2014 all in one place.",B.Fi,"https://github.com/JoeRoganFake/Mental-Warrior-Demo","https://raw.githubusercontent.com/JoeRoganFake/Mental-Warrior-Demo/main/assets/video/Mental_Warrior_Demo.mp4","https://raw.githubusercontent.com/JoeRoganFake/Mental-Warrior-Demo/main/assets/video/Mental_Warrior_Demo_preview.gif","assets/images/mental_warrior_logo.png","People who want to improve themselves \u2014 students, young adults, anyone working on fitness, productivity, or mental well-being \u2014 feel unmotivated, overwhelmed, or stuck. They rely on multiple disconnected apps and struggle to stay consistent.","Built a unified self-improvement platform with structured daily habit tracking, mindset tools, and progress visibility. Offline-first with SQLite so the app works reliably without an internet connection, with a clear path to scale with Firebase sync.","Flutter chosen for cross-platform reach (Android + iOS) from a single codebase. SQLite used for fast, offline-first local storage ensuring the app works without connectivity. Architecture designed to be Firebase-ready for future cloud sync and user accounts.","The biggest challenge was designing a habit system that felt motivating rather than overwhelming \u2014 too many habits leads to burnout. Solved with a focused daily view and streak-based progress to keep users engaged without overloading them.","Live on Google Play Store with an active early-access tester community. Open source on GitHub. Available to the public via the Mental Warrior Testers group.")
B.Ga=A.b(s(["Flutter","SQLite","Local Notifications"]),t.s)
B.K9=new A.yM("aqua_track","Aqua Track","A hydration tracking app built in just 3 days that adjusts your daily water goal based on your current climate, with a built-in intake calculator and smart reminders \u2014 making personalised hydration effortless.",B.Ga,"https://github.com/JoeRoganFake/Aqua-Track-Demo","https://raw.githubusercontent.com/JoeRoganFake/Aqua-Track-Demo/main/assets/demo/Aqua_Track_Demo.mp4",null,"assets/images/aqua_track_logo.png",'Most people underdrink water without realising it, and generic "drink 8 glasses" advice ignores real factors like heat, humidity, and activity level. Existing apps set the same fixed goal for everyone, leaving users with targets that don\'t fit their lifestyle.',"Built a smart hydration tracker that uses the user's current climate data to dynamically adjust their daily water goal. A built-in intake calculator factors in body weight, activity, and temperature to give a personalised recommendation. One-tap logging and visual progress make it satisfying to stay on track.","Flutter for a smooth cross-platform experience. SQLite for lightweight offline-first local storage. Local notifications to send non-intrusive hydration reminders throughout the day.","The biggest challenge was building the climate-aware goal engine and intake calculator accurately within a 3-day timeline. Prioritised a clean, focused feature set and deferred non-essentials to ship a polished core experience fast.","Built and completed in 3 days. Currently in development for release on Google Play Store.")
